WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.328 --> 00:00:13.360
In the ocean,
在海洋里

2
00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:15.200
what is the common point
石油，塑料和放射性物质

3
00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:20.968
between oil, plastic and radioactivity?
有什么共同点呢？

4
00:00:20.968 --> 00:00:26.185
On the top line, this is the BP oil spill:
最上面一行是 BP 公司的石油泄漏

5
00:00:26.185 --> 00:00:28.208
billions of barrels of oil gushing
数十亿桶石油迸发而出

6
00:00:28.208 --> 00:00:29.577
in the Gulf of Mexico.
倾泻在墨西哥湾

7
00:00:29.577 --> 00:00:31.752
The middle line is millions of tons of
中间那行是数百万吨

8
00:00:31.752 --> 00:00:34.156
plastic debris accumulating in our ocean,
塑料废物堆积在我们的海洋中

9
00:00:34.156 --> 00:00:36.876
and the third line is radioactive material
第三行是从福岛核电站

10
00:00:36.876 --> 00:00:39.172
leaking from Fukushima nuclear power plant
泄漏到太平洋的

11
00:00:39.172 --> 00:00:40.510
in the Pacific Ocean.
放射性物质

12
00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:45.093
Well, the three big problems have in common
所以， 这三个严重问题的共同点就是

13
00:00:45.093 --> 00:00:47.908
that they are man-made problems
它们都是人类造成的问题

14
00:00:47.908 --> 00:00:49.964
but they are controlled by natural forces.
但它们都受自然力量所控制

15
00:00:49.964 --> 00:00:54.372
This should make us feel very, terribly awful
这应该使我们感到非常难受

16
00:00:54.372 --> 00:00:56.699
as much as it should make us feel hopeful,
但它也应该使我们感到希望

17
00:00:56.699 --> 00:00:59.508
because if we have the power to create these problems,
因为如果我们有造成这些问题的能力

18
00:00:59.508 --> 00:01:01.188
we may as well have the power
我们也许就同样有能力

19
00:01:01.188 --> 00:01:02.620
to remediate these problems.
解决这些问题

20
00:01:02.620 --> 00:01:04.564
But what about natural forces?
但是自然的力量该怎么办呢？

21
00:01:04.564 --> 00:01:07.547
Well, that's exactly what I want to talk about today,
这正是我今天想要说的

22
00:01:07.547 --> 00:01:09.852
is how we can use these natural forces
就是我们该怎样利用自然的力量

23
00:01:09.852 --> 00:01:15.075
to remediate these man-made problems.
来解决人为问题

24
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:16.301
When the BP oil spill happened,
当BP公司的石油泄漏的时候

25
00:01:16.301 --> 00:01:19.066
I was working at MIT, and I was in charge
我正在MIT工作， 而且我负责

26
00:01:19.066 --> 00:01:21.463
of developing an oil spill-cleaning technology.
研发一项清理石油泄漏的科技

27
00:01:21.463 --> 00:01:24.876
And I had a chance to go in the Gulf of Mexico
我有机会去墨西哥湾

28
00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:27.213
and meet some fishermen and see
去见一些渔民

29
00:01:27.213 --> 00:01:29.004
the terrible conditions in which they were working.
去看看他们工作的恶劣环境

30
00:01:29.004 --> 00:01:32.085
More than 700 of these boats,
超过700艘渔船

31
00:01:32.085 --> 00:01:34.392
which are fishermen boats repurposed
被用作清理油污的船只

32
00:01:34.392 --> 00:01:36.853
with oil absorbent in white
白色的船用来吸收油污

33
00:01:36.853 --> 00:01:39.248
and oil containment in orange, were used,
橘红色的用来装载油污

34
00:01:39.248 --> 00:01:42.507
but they only collected three percent of the oil on the surface,
但他们仅仅清理了漂浮在海洋表面的油污的百分之三

35
00:01:42.507 --> 00:01:44.219
and the health of the cleaners
而那些工作人员的健康

36
00:01:44.219 --> 00:01:46.132
were very deeply affected.
却受到极大的影响

37
00:01:46.132 --> 00:01:50.126
I was working on a very interesting technology
我当时在MIT研发一项有趣的技术

38
00:01:50.126 --> 00:01:52.435
at MIT, but it was a very long-term view
但它是一种关于如何发展技术的

39
00:01:52.435 --> 00:01:53.869
of how to develop technology,
非常长远的观点

40
00:01:53.869 --> 00:01:56.387
and it was going to be a very expensive technology,
而且它会是一项昂贵的技术

41
00:01:56.387 --> 00:01:58.835
and also it would be patented.
它也会被申请专利

42
00:01:58.835 --> 00:02:01.467
So I wanted to develop something that we could
所以我想研发一些发展很快的

43
00:02:01.467 --> 00:02:04.867
develop very fast, that would be cheap,
投入相对小

44
00:02:04.867 --> 00:02:07.307
and that would be open-source, so, because
并且开源的技术

45
00:02:07.307 --> 00:02:09.475
oil spills are not only happening in the Gulf of Mexico,
因为原油泄漏并不仅仅发生在墨西哥湾

46
00:02:09.475 --> 00:02:12.091
and that would be using renewable energy.
而且那会使用可再生能源

47
00:02:12.091 --> 00:02:14.491
So I quit my dream job,
所以我放弃了我梦想的工作

48
00:02:14.491 --> 00:02:16.107
and I moved to New Orleans,
搬去新奥尔良

49
00:02:16.107 --> 00:02:19.051
and I kept on studying how the oil spill was happening.
我继续学习石油泄漏是怎样发生的

50
00:02:19.051 --> 00:02:21.123
Currently, what they were doing is
目前，他们所做的是

51
00:02:21.123 --> 00:02:22.769
that they were using these small fishing boats,
用这些小渔船来清理

52
00:02:22.769 --> 00:02:25.929
and they were cleaning clean lines in an ocean of dirt.
而且他们只是在大片被污染的海洋中清理出几条干净的航线

53
00:02:25.929 --> 00:02:29.642
If you're using the exact same amount of surface
如果你用同样面积的

54
00:02:29.642 --> 00:02:31.795
of oil absorbent, but you're just paying attention
原油吸收船，但你会注意到

55
00:02:31.795 --> 00:02:34.128
to natural patterns, and if you're going up the winds,
更自然的模式，如果你逆风航行

56
00:02:34.128 --> 00:02:35.896
you can collect a lot more material.
就能收集到更多原油

57
00:02:35.896 --> 00:02:38.017
If you're multiplying the rig,
如果你增加船只

58
00:02:38.017 --> 00:02:40.592
so you multiply how many layers of absorbent
你就能增加吸收材料的层数

59
00:02:40.592 --> 00:02:42.494
you're using, you can collect a lot more.
那你就能收集到更多更多的原油

60
00:02:42.494 --> 00:02:45.095
But it's extremely difficult to move oil absorbent
但让吸收原油的船

61
00:02:45.095 --> 00:02:48.727
against the winds, the surface currents and the waves.
逆着风向，洋流和海浪航行是极其困难的

62
00:02:48.727 --> 00:02:50.191
These are enormous forces.
那些都是非常强大的力量

63
00:02:50.191 --> 00:02:53.214
So the very simple idea was to use the ancient technique
所以最简单的方法是用古代的科技

64
00:02:53.214 --> 00:02:55.467
of sailing and tacking of the wind
来航行和改变航向

65
00:02:55.467 --> 00:02:58.085
to capture or intercept the oil
从而收集或拦截

66
00:02:58.085 --> 00:02:59.427
that is drifting down the wind.
顺着风向蔓延的原油

67
00:02:59.427 --> 00:03:02.924
So this didn't require any invention.
这并不需要任何发明

68
00:03:02.924 --> 00:03:04.627
We just took a simple sailing boat
我们只是拿一艘简单的帆船

69
00:03:04.627 --> 00:03:06.524
and we tried to pull something long and heavy,
然后设法让它拖着一些又长又重的东西

70
00:03:06.524 --> 00:03:08.836
but as we tacked back and forth,
但当我们来回穿梭的时候

71
00:03:08.836 --> 00:03:10.507
what we lost was two things:
我们无法保持两件事

72
00:03:10.507 --> 00:03:13.884
we were losing pulling power and direction.
我们失去了拉动力和方向

73
00:03:13.884 --> 00:03:17.716
And so, I thought, what about if we just take the rudder
所以我想，我们把船舵

74
00:03:17.716 --> 00:03:19.228
from the back of the boat to the front,
从船后面拿到前面来会怎么样呢？

75
00:03:19.228 --> 00:03:20.971
would we have better control?
我们能控制的更好吗？

76
00:03:20.971 --> 00:03:23.187
So I built this small sailing robot
所以我做了这只小帆船机器人

77
00:03:23.187 --> 00:03:24.435
with the rudder at the front,
它的舵在前面

78
00:03:24.435 --> 00:03:26.900
and I was trying to pull something very long and heavy,
我试图拖曳一些又长又重的东西

79
00:03:26.900 --> 00:03:30.107
so that's a four-meter-long object just to pull,
所以要拖的是个四米长的物体

80
00:03:30.107 --> 00:03:33.019
