只是看看它是如何工作的

137
00:05:40.077 --> 00:05:42.762
And then we mounted a camera for controlling it,
我们装了一架摄像机来控制它

138
00:05:42.762 --> 00:05:45.664
but quickly we saw that we would need
但很快我们就发现

139
00:05:45.664 --> 00:05:47.813
a lot more weight at the bottom,
底部需要更多重量

140
00:05:47.813 --> 00:05:49.350
so we had to take it back to the lab,
所以我们只好把它拿回实验室

141
00:05:49.350 --> 00:05:51.438
and then we built a skin around it,
并给它装上外壳

142
00:05:51.438 --> 00:05:54.725
we put batteries, remote controllers, and then
我们装了电池，遥控器

143
00:05:54.725 --> 00:05:56.173
we put it in the water and then we
然后我们把它放在水中，接着我们

144
00:05:56.173 --> 00:05:59.334
let it go in the water and see how well it would work,
让它在水中自由航行，看它工作的有多好

145
00:05:59.334 --> 00:06:02.758
so let some rope out, and hope it's going to work,
我们拿掉绳子，希望它能运转的很好

146
00:06:02.758 --> 00:06:05.981
and it worked okay, but we still have a long way.
它运行的还行，但我们还有很长的路要走

147
00:06:05.981 --> 00:06:08.417
Our small prototype has given us good insight
我们的小模型让我们相信

148
00:06:08.417 --> 00:06:09.763
that it's working very well,
这项技术会发展的很好

149
00:06:09.763 --> 00:06:12.448
but we still need to work a lot more on this.
但我们还是有很多工作要做

150
00:06:12.448 --> 00:06:16.317
So what we are doing is an accelerated evolution
所以我们现在所做的

151
00:06:16.317 --> 00:06:17.765
of sailing technology.
是对帆船的改进科技

152
00:06:17.765 --> 00:06:19.692
We went from a back rudder to a front rudder
我们从后置船舵到前置船舵

